commit_message:

This makes build to not include .mo files if they have been created
previously with compile_catalog.

subject: Fix listing of SLO manifest bytes after POST or COPY
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-11-23 17:46:14.000000000', 'files': ['swift/common/middleware/slo.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_slo.py', 'test/functional/tests.py', 'test/unit/container/test_server.py', 'swift/proxy/controllers/obj.py'], 'message': "Fix listing of SLO manifest bytes after POST or COPY

SLO middleware appends a swift_bytes param to the content-type of
manifests, expecting the container server to extract its value and
return it as the object size in container listings.

The SLO copy_hook is not copying swift_bytes from a source manifest
to a destination manifest during a regular COPY or a post-as-copy
request. This results in the wrong size appearing in the container
listing for a manifest that has been COPYed or POSTed to.

This patch modifies the copy-hook to copy across any swift_bytes
from the source response to the sink request. Since the swift_bytes
param is currently removed from content-type in the object controller
GET path, this patch also relocates the call to clean_content_type from
the object controller to the SLO GET handler. That means that swift_bytes
is available to the SLO copy_hook, but now it won't be cleaned up if SLO
is ever removed from the proxy pipeline.

There is very little test coverage for the handling of the
swift_bytes param. This patch adds a unit test for the container
server and some functional tests for the SLO scenarios.

Partial-Bug: #1260446

Change-Id: Ie21a3c0c9bcb7eaf85f392ae97be496ff8a2ee34
"}]
commit_message:
Fix listing of SLO manifest bytes after POST or COPY

SLO middleware appends a swift_bytes param to the content-type of
manifests, expecting the container server to extract its value and
return it as the object size in container listings.

The SLO copy_hook is not copying swift_bytes from a source manifest
to a destination manifest during a regular COPY or a post-as-copy
request. This results in the wrong size appearing in the container
listing for a manifest that has been COPYed or POSTed to.

This patch modifies the copy-hook to copy across any swift_bytes
from the source response to the sink request. Since the swift_bytes
param is currently removed from content-type in the object controller
GET path, this patch also relocates the call to clean_content_type from
the object controller to the SLO GET handler. That means that swift_bytes
is available to the SLO copy_hook, but now it won't be cleaned up if SLO
is ever removed from the proxy pipeline.

There is very little test coverage for the handling of the
swift_bytes param. This patch adds a unit test for the container
server and some functional tests for the SLO scenarios.

Partial-Bug: #1260446

Change-Id: Ie21a3c0c9bcb7eaf85f392ae97be496ff8a2ee34

commit_message:
Allow resources to delay polling

Provide an easy way for resource types to limit the rate at which they are
polled, by raising a PollDelay exception from a check_<ACTION>_complete()
method, without having to maintain their own state.

commit_message:
Replace safe_utils.getcallargs with inspect.getcallargs

safe_utils.getcallargs was written to support python2.6 which did not
have inspect.getcallargs.  Now that support for python2.6 has been
dropped it should be replaced with inspect.getcallargs.

Note:The interface that safe_utils.getcallargs provides did not match
inspect.getcallargs around the handling of the self parameter needing to
be passed in. It should be brought inline with inspect.getcallargs so
that it can be dropped. Nova fixed in 2910d75b28afd909af3b4ac392729ac3d5e64b65.

Change-Id: I2fbec0cc4d43b2fc424460b176bf26700f05f44a

subject: Reduce READ_FREQ and TIMEOUT for watch-file
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-05-18 17:39:43.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_log/tests/unit/test_log.py', 'oslo_log/watchers.py'], 'message': 'Reduce READ_FREQ and TIMEOUT for watch-file

The watch-file option currently relies on pyinotify which makes
use of select.poll. This is eventlet incompatible so it blocks
the whole thread for TIMEOUT milliseconds every READ_FREQ seconds.

This meant that an agent/service using this option is blocked for
500 milliseconds every 1 second.

Until a non-blocking alternative can be found, this adjusts the
READ_FREQ and TIMEOUT params on the FastWatchedFileHandler to
3 and 5 respectively. So every 3 seconds, it will block for 5
milliseconds so only 0.16% of time is lost instead of 50%.

Change-Id: I6fdc0a3f1eaae39eb86440c6c4b07ca8d91f2462
Partial-Bug: #1583270
'}]
commit_message:
Reduce READ_FREQ and TIMEOUT for watch-file

The watch-file option currently relies on pyinotify which makes
use of select.poll. This is eventlet incompatible so it blocks
the whole thread for TIMEOUT milliseconds every READ_FREQ seconds.

This meant that an agent/service using this option is blocked for
500 milliseconds every 1 second.

Until a non-blocking alternative can be found, this adjusts the
READ_FREQ and TIMEOUT params on the FastWatchedFileHandler to
3 and 5 respectively. So every 3 seconds, it will block for 5
milliseconds so only 0.16% of time is lost instead of 50%.

Change-Id: I6fdc0a3f1eaae39eb86440c6c4b07ca8d91f2462
Partial-Bug: #1583270

commit_message:
Fix compare_obj() to obey missing/unset fields

When comparing objects to dicts, if a field is unset on both, they
should still be counted as equal. If something is unset on one, but not
on the other, they should be counted as unequal. In any of these
situations, if the field is set in allow_missing, all of the equality
checks should just be skipped.

Change-Id: I3e5143bc872ab4cb645d09c7e969fd1cf9c7985c
Closes-Bug: #1566398

commit_message:
Deprecate verbose option in logging

Option "verbose" from group "DEFAULT" is deprecated for removal.
The parameter has no effect.
Deprecated verbose for logging and init
Remove verbose in README
Remove verbose from tests.
If this option is not set explicitly, there is no such warning.

commit_message:
Introduce support for oslo.messaging amqp driver configuration

This commit adds support for the oslo.messaging amqp rpc_backend
which enables the AMQP 1.0 driver. A proposed feature for the
Newton oslo.messaging release is an update to the AMQP 1.0 driver
to support a stateless messaging interconnect for RPC traffic [1].

This patch:
* use oslo::messaging::amqp resource
* add new parameters for the oslo_messaging_amqp driver
* update spec tests for amqp as alternate rpc_backend
* add feature release note

[1] https://blueprints.launchpad.net/oslo.messaging/+spec/amqp-dispatch-router

Change-Id: I1bda9eb255e4e810f349c49780a34b116ea18a14

commit_message:
oidc: DRY when obtaining an access token

Obtanining the access token from the access token URL is done in the
same way, regardless of the grant_type being used, with the only
difference of the payload exchanged. This change tries to remove
duplicated code.

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-05-19 12:55:12.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/install-guide/ops-galera-recovery.rst'], 'message': 'Docs: Add note about slow galera recovery

Rebuilding a galera container is stressful enough and deployers
may find that restarting the MariaDB daemon on a re-created
container takes a lot of time.

This patch adds a note to advise deployers about the time required to
sync data from the older nodes to the new, empty node. This will hopefully
restore some sanity and alleviate some stress.

Change-Id: Ife5ffed913e7ca21f7d003b7f09b740e1f678a21
'}]
commit_message:
Docs: Add note about slow galera recovery

Rebuilding a galera container is stressful enough and deployers
may find that restarting the MariaDB daemon on a re-created
container takes a lot of time.

This patch adds a note to advise deployers about the time required to
sync data from the older nodes to the new, empty node. This will hopefully
restore some sanity and alleviate some stress.

Change-Id: Ife5ffed913e7ca21f7d003b7f09b740e1f678a21

commit_message:
Wait for loadbalancer to be ready instead of sleeping

This makes the creation of resources in the sample Vagrant
configuration less dependent on the host resources or hypervisor
execution time.

Before this, the local.sh was randomnly failing at any of it's steps
in my environment.

Change-Id: Ie3795a1f9244b46f5b6469107ad1d03f087a64ed

commit_message:
Add other-requirements.txt for bindep

Bindep is a binary automation tool used in openstack-infra.  With it,
projects can better control the default packages installed into the
OS. Because we are using puppet, we actually don't want any packages
installed by default as to better test our manifests.

Change-Id: Ic8e4334cee48a3ef604c3aa062539e6fe3b32232
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

subject: oidc: Remove unused parameters in _OidcBase
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-05-19 15:16:21.000000000', 'files': ['keystoneauth1/identity/v3/oidc.py', 'keystoneauth1/tests/unit/identity/test_identity_v3_oidc.py'], 'message': 'oidc: Remove unused parameters in _OidcBase

Some methods in _OidcBase accepted a parameter to indicate the URL where
a request was to be made:

- _get_keystone_token accepted federated_token_url, the URL for
  federated authentication.
- _get_access_token accepted access_token_endpoint, the URL used to get
  an oidc access token.

However, the methods were using internally the object attribute
self.access_token_endpoint and the property self.federated_token_url,
therefore the parameters were completely ignored. This changes removes
them and adjust the derived classes.

Change-Id: Ibc2157d47cb0edd59c4d966bae77c102423f97ae
'}]
commit_message:
oidc: Remove unused parameters in _OidcBase

Some methods in _OidcBase accepted a parameter to indicate the URL where
a request was to be made:

- _get_keystone_token accepted federated_token_url, the URL for
  federated authentication.
- _get_access_token accepted access_token_endpoint, the URL used to get
  an oidc access token.

However, the methods were using internally the object attribute
self.access_token_endpoint and the property self.federated_token_url,
therefore the parameters were completely ignored. This changes removes
them and adjust the derived classes.

Change-Id: Ibc2157d47cb0edd59c4d966bae77c102423f97ae

commit_message:
crypto - wrap random body key

use a random key to encrypt the object body, wrap that body key
with keymaster provided object key and persist wrapped key in
object sysmeta header for crypto meta.

Wrap using AES CTR mode with IV, not aes_wrap_key algorithm,
for performance.

Change-Id: I4c2ba12dd35bb3f4951dce65bc7f488a332e0c18

commit_message:
Add tests for floating_ip private functions

There are 2 try/except blocks within _translate_floating_ip_view() that
cause in different resulting dictionaries. These situations are
untested, so now we can test for different scenarios of missing
attributes on the floating IP. An if check was also added to the
function because the types passed in are objects, so if the attribute is
not set on the object, it raises a NotImplementedError. So instead of
catching that too, we check to see if the key is in the object (which
checks if it is set).

Change-Id: Ia5739f214f57525b3083ef3f201f6f08198703e5

commit_message:
Fix cleaning boot sectors of disks on delete

Bootloaders may check MBR signature to determine,
if it can boot from thios disk. So let's clear it
together with boot code.

Also #{dev[:name]} is just a name of a device, like
sdb, so add /dev/ path.

Change-Id: Ifc23fe4e4919a10b3d5546c98ee333ccac9c92f2
(cherry picked from commit 3c00fb65501235692af2c586bb113e7bb37e5039)

commit_message:
Update openstack-ansible-security role SHA

The role openstack-ansible-security has been updated to fix several
bugs. This commit updates the version used by openstack-ansible to the
head of the liberty branch.

This commit switches from using a tag to using a SHA to allow future
updates of the version consumed to be done as part of the standard
release process by which all other SHAs are updated.

Change-Id: I812aa3642a7f62761a70006a4e5d312f4b7bad2c

commit_message:
Complete Nova support for Glance's v2

Glance v1 is subject to deprecation, we need Nova to move away
from v1 and use v2 fully. This spec discusses how we plan to
make that transition. This also documents the testing plan
for both v1 and v2 and few limitations associated with it.

Previously-approved: Mitaka

commit_message:
Reword the note following microversion headers

I had to read the original note four times before it made sense to me.
The problem, I think, was that it talked about 'old' and 'new' - but I
don't have enough context to immediately remember which is old and which
is new. Also, the new thing was first, and my brain wanted to make them
be listed in the opposite order. It was also unclear to me for a bit
which was the one I was supposed to use.

Address those concerns by rewording the note to be clear that the first
option is the desired one, and to refer to each of them as first and
second rather than old and new.

Change-Id: I1d51572eb57278e6b21224ca60516c528de42ee1

commit_message:
Nailgun Fixes for smart configuration changes support

Simply unhardcode the handler for $.configuration namespace
to allow a user to modify anything he wants in this namespace.
The list of modifyable sections on '$.configuration' namespace of astute.yaml
should not be hardcoded - this makes no sense as support of these pieces
is implemented on fuel library and plugins side. Hardcoding the list
will make it impossible for a plugin developer to reuse configuration
changes feature to support configuration options for plugin.

DocImpact

Partial-bug: #1580522

Change-Id: I4eb18461c0a4f337b649abfcd099259965290ff5

commit_message:
Provide package update and toggle_public with glance_client

Due to the changes in client for maintaining visibility
consistency between packages and images we need to pass glance
client to update and toggle_public method calls.
Also this patch adds warning for the user that other packages
will also become public.

Change-Id: I0c95bc0abf6e597f4dd6934ae423e0f8111c3cc5
Depends-on: I7b673c40595ce730b5da83877279ee70ac37924b
Partial-bug: #1509208

subject: Maintain visibility consistency for packages and images
revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2016-05-18 13:25:48.000000000', 'files': ['muranoclient/common/utils.py', 'muranoclient/v1/shell.py', 'muranoclient/tests/unit/test_shell.py', 'muranoclient/v1/artifact_packages.py', 'muranoclient/v1/packages.py'], 'message': 'Maintain visibility consistency for packages and images

This change adds code that ensures that if package is made public,
all its dependencies (required packages and images) are also made
public. It allows to avoid bad user experience for a tenant having
access to a package but not to its dependencies in case of turning
private packages into public.
Change is made in muranoclient to provide the same behaviour while
changing package visibility through dashboard or through CLI.

Change-Id: I7b673c40595ce730b5da83877279ee70ac37924b
Partial-bug: #1509208

commit_message:
Maintain visibility consistency for packages and images

This change adds code that ensures that if package is made public,
all its dependencies (required packages and images) are also made
public. It allows to avoid bad user experience for a tenant having
access to a package but not to its dependencies in case of turning
private packages into public.
Change is made in muranoclient to provide the same behaviour while
changing package visibility through dashboard or through CLI.

Change-Id: I7b673c40595ce730b5da83877279ee70ac37924b
Partial-bug: #1509208

commit_message:
Align the stars to bump CI to latest Newton

1) scenario001: disable ceilometer tests on Ubuntu
Because we need this backport in UCA:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/318503/
And we won't have it before... who knows?
Let's disable the tests for Ceilometer on Ubuntu until UCA provides a
packaging update.
Let's also disable Telemetry at all on Ubuntu, since Ceilometer can't be
tested until UCA does the backport.

2) add RDO Newton dependencies repository, so we have paramiko >= 2.0
and have a more stable gate.

3) Update RDO trunk URL to have a very recent URL.

4) Update nova endpoints to match with what is required upstream (2.1)

5) Un-pin Tempest, so we keep testing master (our desire in our master
gate but we pin it in stable branches).

Change-Id: I10dc1beeca3ec47fd4c3a866aa3e1d3bc9d0aa81

commit_message:
wait until node boot completely before reboot

Reboot hook is used to reboot node with bootstrap image
or provisioned node. It's possible that this hook is called
when boot process of provisioned node haven't completed.
Upstart system doesn't handle such situation and node may
hang.

So let's reboot immediately if we're in a bootstrap. Wait until
system boots completely in case of provisioned node. We check it by
existense of /run/cloud-init/status.json (it's located on tmpfs, so
no stale file from previous boot can be found). If this file hasn't
appeared after 60 seconds - reboot as is.

Partial-Bug: #1573105

Change-Id: Iae113425a0034bc137c88db305d405f79807a5dc
(cherry picked from commit 4698918d4e08dbdddc31dda2c2a0a4c71f572aa2)

commit_message:
objects: adding serial, path, bus_address fields to bdm object

Adding fields serial, path, bus_address in the title to the
block device mapping object to be able to form disk metadata.

path - Holds a fix disk path, when used in a container.
serial - user-set serial disk serial string
bus_address - The block device's address as it appears to the guest.
              The format is based on the bus, can be any of the following:
              PCI address, or SCSI address, of USB port, or IDE channel, etc.

Partially implements blueprint virt-device-role-tagging
Co-authored-by: Artom Lifshitz <alifshit@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I7a9902c4a96f98332678068ae53d09b6bd6b06d0

commit_message:
Add authorize method to Enforcer

To facilitate projects wishing to ensure that all policies are
registered before use an authorize method has been added which errors
when checking an unregistered policy. If the policy has been registered
then the enforce method is called in the normal manner.

commit_message:
Add helper methods for generating policy info

This adds two helper methods that consuming projects can use to get
information that helps deployers.

The generate_policy method takes a configured policy.Enforcer and
outputs a yaml formatted policy file for that configuration. This can be
used for audit purposes or to use with a tool like oslopolicy-checker.

The generate_matches method takes a configured policy.Enforcer and
returns a list of policy.PolicyOpt objects for policies defined in a
config file which match registered defaults. This helps deployers winnow
down their configured policies to just those that are actual overrides.

commit_message:
Enable IPAM drivers to allocate from more than one subnet

Calling in to the IPAM driver independently for each subnet on a
network can be costly, especially if the IPAM system is external.
This change opens the possibility of optimizing the operation of
allocating one IP address from a list of candidate subnets by allowing
drivers to subclass the default implementation.

Change-Id: I07b32752e1e2e84641dd6504a93cfef95ae368c5
Partially-Implements: blueprint bp/routed-networks

commit_message:
fix network configuration

When deploying with `network_isolation: true`, we are failing to pass
in the network settings from our configuration into the tripleo
deployment process, leading ultimately to deployment failures when
attempting to use non-default values.

additionally, setting `network_isolation: true` required adding a
number of explicit arguments to `extra_args`, so it was not possible
to control the use of network isolation simply by toggling the value
of `network_isolation`.

This commits allows the deployment to succeed with `network_isolation`
either disabled or enabled, and allows the use of non-default values
for the network configuration.

Change-Id: I68f5a87e390aa2ea8d8c5631eba17dc5dd44270e
Closes-bug: #1581659

commit_message:
Lowercase Compute in an example header

Headers are case insensitive, so case doesn't actually matter. However,
the normal form for compute in the keystone catalog is all lower case -
so seeing it here as leading-caps brings a cognitive dissonance that
isn't valuable.

Change-Id: Ief3e5263b421b1b59165b40a073c9a2fbd321dea

subject: Apply query to highlight query
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-05-19 15:09:34.000000000', 'files': ['searchlight/tests/unit/v1/test_search.py', 'searchlight/api/v1/search.py'], 'message': 'Apply query to highlight query

If not specified, highlighting defaults to attempting to reapply the
entire query to documents successfully matched. Since we apply our RBAC
terms in a filtered_query, the highlighter attempts to include them.

Elasticsearch 2.1 highlights this (pun intended) because highlighting
parent/child queries doesn't work; in ES 1.x it failed silently.
Although the underlying bug for 2.x will likely be fixed (see
https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/14999), the behavior is
wrong.

This patch applies the "query" as "highlight_query" to all highlighted
fields, unless a "highlight_query" is already provided.

Change-Id: I665d629456ee4fa20c194e65b38b198ac0861f1d
Closes-Bug: #1570213
(cherry picked from commit 204d7b4232031517e1da1e3b02f4fc1809813002)
'}]
commit_message:
Apply query to highlight query

If not specified, highlighting defaults to attempting to reapply the
entire query to documents successfully matched. Since we apply our RBAC
terms in a filtered_query, the highlighter attempts to include them.

Elasticsearch 2.1 highlights this (pun intended) because highlighting
parent/child queries doesn't work; in ES 1.x it failed silently.
Although the underlying bug for 2.x will likely be fixed (see
https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/14999), the behavior is
wrong.

This patch applies the "query" as "highlight_query" to all highlighted
fields, unless a "highlight_query" is already provided.

Change-Id: I665d629456ee4fa20c194e65b38b198ac0861f1d
Closes-Bug: #1570213
(cherry picked from commit 204d7b4232031517e1da1e3b02f4fc1809813002)
